        <name>ACL Instructions</name>
        <static_content><![CDATA[<p> </p>
<p>To ensure that this ACL is properly configured, make sure that:</p>
<ul style="list-style-position: inside;"><li>A <strong>suitable</strong> <strong>role</strong> is <strong>added</strong> under &#34;Required roles&#34;</li><li>If <strong>public access</strong> is <strong>required</strong>, you should set <strong>add</strong> the <strong>public</strong> role <strong>explictily</strong></li><li>If <strong>adding</strong> a <strong>role</strong> is <strong>not</strong> <strong>possible</strong> and <strong>no Script</strong> is <strong>present</strong>, <strong>set</strong> the <strong>ACL</strong> to &#34;<strong>Advanced &#61; true</strong>&#34; and <strong>add</strong> the following <strong>script</strong>:<br />
<pre style="width: 640px;">answer &#61; gs.getSession().isLoggedIn();
if (!answer) {
    answer &#61; gs.getProperty(&#39;glide.security.allow_unauth_roleless_acl&#39;, false);
}</pre>
</li></ul>
<p>ServiceNow Resources:<br /><a href="https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/vancouver-platform-security/page/administer/contextual-security/concept/acl-rule-types.html#acl-rule-types__fig_ey1_kn2_2r" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">ACL Evaluation ➚</a> (ServiceNow Docs)<br /><a href="https://support.servicenow.com/kb?id&#61;kb_article_view&amp;sysparm_article&#61;KB1555339" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">KB1555339 ➚</a> (ACL Maintenance)<br /><a href="https://support.servicenow.com/kb?id&#61;kb_article_view&amp;sysparm_article&#61;KB1555340" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">KB1555340 ➚</a> (Self Hosted ACL Maintenance)</p>]]></static_content>
